                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode4/centralize-error-response.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>In the <code>EventListener</code> directory, we created an <code>ApiExceptionSubscriber</code> whose job
is to catch all exceptions and turn them into nice API problem responses. And it
already has all of the logic we need to turn an <code>ApiProblem</code> object into a proper
response:</p>
