	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2832243510" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Yo Chuck!</p><p>Yep, you've got it exactly - I won't even re-summarize because you described it perfectly :).</p><p>But, btw - there's a lazy way to handle authentication with JS: if you have a traditional server-side login form that uses cookies to log you in (i.e. the way we've been logging people in for 15 years), then if you make AJAX calls from React or anything else, it will automatically be authenticated because it sends the session cookie. This would no longer be a pure, 100% client-side app, but honestly, I think sometimes when people are building an API just to support their JS frontend, they don't realize this is also an option :).</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
